403":"1403","1358":"1358","1412":"1412","1401":"1401","Abt 1354":"omkring 1354","1475":"1475","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","after 1340":"efter 1340","England":"England, United Kingdom","Alt Yr Ynyc, Walterstone, Ewyas, Herfordshire, England":"Walterstone, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","Burleigh, Gloucestershire, England":"Burleigh, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"after 1340–1395":"na 1340–1395","1340–1395":"1340–1395","–Male":"Overleden","1375–Female":"1375–Overleden","1338–1420":"1338–1420","1401–Male":"1401–Overleden","1403–Male":"1403–Overleden","1412–Male":"1412–Overleden","1370–1475":"1370–1475","1358–Male":"1358–Overleden","1360–Female":"1360–Overleden","1395":"1395","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1370":"1370","1338":"1338","1403":"1403","1358":"1358","1412":"1412","1401":"1401","Abt 1354":"circa 1354","1475":"1475","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","after 1340":"na 1340","England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Alt Yr Ynyc, Walterstone, Ewyas, Herfordshire, England":"Walterstone, Herefordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Burleigh, Gloucestershire, England":"Burleigh, Gloucestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"after 1340–1395":"after 1340–1395","1340–1395":"1340–1395","–Male":"Deceased","1375–Female":"1375–Deceased","1338–1420":"1338–1420","1401–Male":"1401–Deceased","1403–Male":"1403–Deceased","1412–Male":"1412–Deceased","1370–1475":"1370–1475","1358–Male":"1358–Deceased","1360–Female":"1360–Deceased","1395":"1395","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1370":"1370","1338":"1338","1403":"1403","1358":"1358","1412":"1412","1401":"1401","Abt 1354":"about 1354","1475":"1475","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","after 1340":"after 1340","England":"England, United Kingdom","Alt Yr Ynyc, Walterstone, Ewyas, Herfordshire, England":"Walterstone, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","Burleigh, Gloucestershire, England":"Burleigh, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Cecil","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Welsh (Monmouthshire): from the Old Welsh personal name <i>Seisyllt</i>, sometimes wrongly said to derive from the Latin name <i>Caecilius</i> (see   Sisley  ). The most frequent modern spelling is a Renaissance attempt to connect the surname with <i>Caecilius</i> in the English pronunciation of its time. The Welsh name is more probably, but not definitely, from the Latin name <i>Sextilius</i>, a derivative of <i>sextus</i> ‘sixth’.","History: The great and powerful English Cecil family first came to prominence with David Cecil, a Monmouthshire gentleman who espoused the cause of Henry Tudor and came to court in London after the latter became king in 1485. His grandson William Cecil, Lord Burghley (1520–98), was Elizabeth I's chief adviser for 40 years, and his descendants have remained politically powerful and culturally influential in Britain ever since. They were originally minor Welsh gentry; their name is found in a variety of forms, including <i>Sitsylt</i>, <i>Ceyssel</i>, and <i>Sisseld</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Cissell","meanings":["English (Middlesex): variant of Welsh   Cecil  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Sisley","meanings":["English (Kent): from the popular Middle English female personal name <i>Sisely</i> (Old French <i>Cecile</i>, <i>Cicile</i>, from Latin <i>Caecilia</i>, feminine form of the Roman surname <i>Caecilius</i>, a derivative of <i>caecus</i> ‘blind’). This was the name of a early Christian virgin martyr of the 2nd or 3rd century, who came to be regarded as the patron saint of music. The surname is generally spelt with <i>C-</i> in the Middle Ages, following the trend of the personal name, and with <i>S-</i> in modern times. Compare   Cecil   and see also   Sise  ,   Sisson  ."]},{"name":"Cissel","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Cecil  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Cecil was born after 1340, in Walterstone, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Robert ap Seisyll, was 8642 and his mother, Siesyll, was 8640. He married Margred Wynston verch Gilbert about 1354. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1395, in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"after 1340–1395":"pärast 1340–1395","1340–1395":"1340–1395","–Male":"Surnud","1375–Female":"1375–Surnud","1338–1420":"1338–1420","1401–Male":"1401–Surnud","1403–Male":"1403–Surnud","1412–Male":"1412–Surnud","1370–1475":"1370–1475","1358–Male":"1358–Surnud","1360–Female":"1360–Surnud","1395":"1395","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1370":"1370","1338":"1338","1403":"1403","1358":"1358","1412":"1412","1401":"1401","Abt 1354":"umbes 1354","1475":"1475","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","after 1340":"pärast 1340","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Alt Yr Ynyc, Walterstone, Ewyas, Herfordshire, England":"Walterstone, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Burleigh, Gloucestershire, England":"Burleigh, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"after 1340–1395":"1340 jälkeen–1395","1340–1395":"1340–1395","–Male":"Kuollut","1375–Female":"1375–Kuollut","1338–1420":"1338–1420","1401–Male":"1401–Kuollut","1403–Male":"1403–Kuollut","1412–Male":"1412–Kuollut","1370–1475":"1370–1475","1358–Male":"1358–Kuollut","1360–Female":"1360–Kuollut","1395":"1395","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1370":"1370","1338":"1338","1403":"1403","1358":"1358","1412":"1412","1401":"1401","Abt 1354":"noin 1354","1475":"1475","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","after